"panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">\r\n         スタッフ          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1368.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> コーディネーター </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> ソーティングチーム </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> 芳田琢磨率いる６人のチームでサイトの維持管理とサンプル回収、ソーティングを担当 </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n           \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n          [:]', '[:en]About[:ja]アバウト[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '19-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-27 08:25:40', '2016-07-27 08:25:40', '', 19, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=632', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(633, 1, '2016-07-27 08:29:27', '2016-07-27 08:29:27', '[:en]<div class="item active">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/slider-sorter.jpg" alt="First slide" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>About</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">OKEON is a network to monitor the terrestrial environment of Okinawa, involving researchers at OIST, collaborators a various institutions, museums and high schools across Okinawa, and the local community.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=19"> Learn More </a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/slider-trap.jpg" alt="slider3" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>Science</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">The main components of OKEON include a field network, sample processing capacity, ecological genomics pipeline, and environmental informatics capacity.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=29"> See More </a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_2331.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>Community</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">OKEON strongly integrates the community as it not only includes institutions, it also involves high schools and museums across Okinawa. OKEON also places great emphasis on environmental education.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=21">Learn More</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/slider-map.png" alt="map4" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>Map</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">The interactive map displays a list of OKEON field sites and collaborators.  </p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=137">See Map </a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>[:ja]<div class="item active">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/slider-sorter.jpg" alt="First slide" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>アバウト</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">OKEON美ら森プロジェクトは沖縄社会連携型の陸域環境モニタリングプロジェクトで、沖縄科学技術大学院大学の研究者、沖縄全島の様々な機関や博物館、高校と地元の皆様と協力をして行っています。</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=19"> Learn More </a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/slider-trap.jpg" alt="slider3" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>科学</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">美ら森プロジェクトは、おもに沖縄島全域を対象とした環境モニタリングネットワーク、サンプル処理システム、生態遺伝学と環境情報の蓄積からなります。</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=29"> See More </a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_2331.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>コミュニティ</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">沖縄社会連携型のプロジェクトなので、大学、高校、博物館などの皆様と協力しています。また、OKEONは環境教育にも力を入れています。</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=21">Learn More</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="item">\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/slider-map.png" alt="map4" />\r\n<div class="carousel-caption">\r\n<h1>地図</h1>\r\n<p class="slider-text">インタラクティブな地図でOKEONのモニタリングサイトや協力者の情報を一覧できます。</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="button3"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?page_id=137">地図へ</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Home[:ja]ホーム[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-27 08:29:27', '2016-07-27 08:29:27', '', 16, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=633', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(634, 1, '2016-07-29 04:03:43', '2016-07-29 04:03:43', '[:en]<div class="row" id="front-icons-wrapper margin-bottom50">\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Achievements</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>Achievement of the OKEON Project Field and Social Networks in FY2015 </h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3> Summary</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n+ 24 research sites with 72 SLAM traps are established.\r\n+ The system is established for collecting the material and data from 72 traps every two weeks and maintaining those traps.\r\n+ The sorting and curatorial systems for the materials are established.\r\n+ Met and had meetings with more than 150+ Okinawan people.\r\n+ Cooperating with 28+ groups.\r\n+ One report in the Research Bulletin of Environmental Education Center, Miyagi University of Education.\r\n+ Nine media releases.\r\n+ Yoshi has been selected as a committee member for an Okinawan prefectural project, the controlling invasive species.\r\n+ Yoshi has been offered having six columns on a newspaper, Ryukyu Shinpo, for six months (once a month).\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Sampling </h3>\r\n\r\n<p> \r\n+ Lab space for sorting material and cabinets for the specimens were set up.\r\n+ 600+ collection events, 6,000+ sorted vials, and more than 180,000+ insect specimens have been accumulated.\r\n+ One technician and six staffs in the sorting team have been hired.\r\n+ The sorting staffs have been quickly trained and more than 90% of the insect samples are sorted into the order level on time.\r\n+ Reference collection of Okinawan ants was gifted from Mr. Takamine.\r\n+ Three undetermined species of ants are recognized from the sample collected in the ants research program at the high schools.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Networking </h3>\r\n<p>\r\nOKEON project has been cooperating with at least 28 groups listed below.\r\n+ Tsuji Lab at University of Ryukyus\r\n	The main counter part for MOU. Two jointed grant proposals have been submitted. Jointed lab meetings were taken place. Planning with them that making theses using material from OKEON project.\r\n+ Subtropical Field Science Center at University of Ryukyus\r\n	Helping establishment of the field sites at Oku, Yona, and two at the Campus in the Univ. of Ryukyus.\r\n+ Ryukyu University Museum, Fujukan\r\n	Giving us advices on the curatorial system, on site localities, and connecting to the Okinawan community of conservation biology.\r\n+ Okinawa Prefectural Museum\r\n	Providing us a cold space for storing specimens. Cooperation on their exhibition is planning.\r\n+ Se-fa Utakim, the world heritage\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Kurashiki Dam\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Nago Central Park\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Nakagusuku Park\r\n	Providing a site. Suggested us some connections in the Okinawan society.\r\n+ Okinawa Prefectural Forest Park\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Heiwasozo-no-mori Park\r\n	Providing a site	\r\n+ Tamagusuku Youth and Children''s Center\r\n	Providing a site, and they are willing the cooperation with us on development of an environmental education program.\r\n+ Hentona High School\r\n	Providing a site. Established an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa.\r\n+ Kyuyo High School\r\n	Established an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa. We found several undetermined ant species in their material.\r\n+ Futenma High School\r\n	Established an ant research team in their biology club program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa. We found an undetermined ant species in their material. It is the species, which is at least the first record in Japan.\r\n+ Kaiho High School\r\nEstablished an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa.\r\n+ Higashi Museum\r\n	Helping us to get the permission to set up a site at the mangrove forest in Higashi son.\r\n+ Community at the mangrove forest in Kesaji Gulf, National Heritage\r\n	They have accepted setting a site up at the mangrove forest area, and planning using the site for the local environmental education.\r\n+ Bird Forest Nature Park, Uruma City\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Nago Museum\r\n	Providing a site and helping us to get the permission to set up a site at the Mt. Katsu-dake in Nago City.\r\n+ Onna-Son Museum\r\n	Discussing the way to cooperation for the research on the natural history in the village.\r\n+ Okinawa City Museum\r\n	Providing a site, and cooperated on their exhibition, helped us to make multiple connections to Okinawan Society, planning cooperation on their new exhibition.\r\n+ Chatan Town Hall\r\n	Providing a site, gave us suggestions for setting soil sensors.\r\n+ Sueyoshi Park (Naha City)\r\n	Providing a site, helped us to find a site in Sueyoshi Park.\r\n+ Mori-no-ie Minmin\r\n	 Helped us to find a site in Sueyoshi Park.\r\n+ Yambaru Discovery Forest\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Southeast Botanical Gardens\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Ohyama Yam Farm\r\n	Providing a site.\r\n+ Mr. Takamine\r\n	Provided the reference collection of Okinawan ants.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Publications </h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Achievements[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '620-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-29 04:03:43', '2016-07-29 04:03:43', '', 620, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=634', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
