(691, 1, '2016-08-02 02:48:01', '2016-08-02 02:48:01', '[:en]<h2 class="section-heading">About </h2>\r\n<hr class="home2 left">\r\n        \r\n\r\n<div class="container">\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="panel-group margin-top100" id="accordion">\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel1">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">\r\n          Project Mission and Goals      \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n       <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1207.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n       </div>\r\n       <div class="row">\r\n                 <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Mission </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  The overall mission of the OKEON Churamori Project is to establish a collaborative network in order to utilize modern techniques to measure, monitor, and understand the terrestrial environment of Okinawa, to conduct scientific research, and to help conserve the environment by working with the community and providing educational opportunities.</p>\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Goals </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  \r\n                       1. Establish a terrestrial environmental monitoring network in Okinawa\r\n                       2. Develop a system for processing samples\r\n                       3. Accumulate data on Okinawa biodiversity\r\n                       4. Establish an environmental education network in Okinawa\r\n                      \r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n\r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel3">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">\r\n         Current Status          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1368.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Current Status </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> Thus far the OKEON team have set up 24 sites, 72 traps (three at each site), 24 weather stations (one at each site). </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel2">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">\r\n         Staff          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1368.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Unit Leader </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Evan Economo </b>  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Project Leader </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Masashi Yoshimura </b> <i>Coordinator</i> </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Assistants </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"><b> Masako Osagawara </b> <i>Executive Assistant</i> </p>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Aina Urano </b> <i>Assistant</i> </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Sorting Team </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Takuma Yoshida </b> <i>Taxonomist / Sorting Technician</i></p> \r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-left-right-20">He leads a team of six sorters undertaking tasks including setting up sites, collecting samples, arthropod identification and sorting, and data entry.</p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Linda Iha </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Shinji Iriyama </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Toshihiro Kinjo </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Izumi Maehira </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Yasutaka Tamaki </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Kozue Uekama </b> <i>Sorter</i></p> \r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Miyagi Akino </b> <i> (Past) Sorter</i></p> \r\n\r\n                   \r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Database and Website </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <b> Julia Janicki </b> <i> Computing Technician</i></p> \r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel4">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">\r\n          Partners     \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n          <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_0996.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="row">\r\n                 <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> OIST </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> OKEON Churamori Project is fully funded by Okinawa Institute of Science and Technology. </p>\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Partners </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> Uruma City、Oogimi Village、Ohyama Yam Farm、Okinawa Prefectural Government、Okinawa Prefectural Government Education Department、Okinawa Prefectural Museum, Okinawa Prefectural Government Northern Okinawa Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries Center、Urasoe High School、Kyuyo High School、Okinawa Prefectural Education Center、Shuri High School、Nago High School、Futenma High School、Hentona High School、Okinawa International University、Okinawa Zoo and Museum、Okinawa City、Okinawa City Local Museum、Okinawa Times、Onna Village, Onna-son Museum、California Academy of Sciences、Kunigami Village、Kyushu Research Center、Typhoon FM、Hidetsune Takamine、Kenji Takehara、Tamagusuku Youth and Children''s Center、Natural History Museum and Institute- Chiba、Chatan Town Hall、TBS、Southeast Botanical Gardens、Nakagusuku Park、Nago City Katsuyama、Nago City、Nago Museum、Nanjo City、Higashi Village、Higashi Museum、Gesaji Ward Council 、Museum of Nature and Human Activities、Hokkaido University、The Hokkaido University Museum、Madagascar Biodiversity Center、Mori-no-ie Minmin、Yambaru Discovery Forest、Yambaru Wildlife Conservation Center、Ryukyu Shinpo、University of the Ryukyus、Ryukyu Broadcasting Corp\r\n\r\n　　　　　　　　　　　</p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n    \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>           \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n          [:ja]<h2 class="section-heading">OKEON美ら森プロジェクトとは </h2>\r\n<hr class="home2 left">\r\n        \r\n\r\n<div class="container">\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="panel-group margin-top100" id="accordion">\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel1">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">\r\n          プロジェクトが目指すもの  \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n       <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1207.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n       </div>\r\n       <div class="row">\r\n                 <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> ミッション </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  The overall mission of the OKEON Churamori Project is to establish a collaborative network in order to utilize modern techniques to measure, monitor, and understand the terrestrial environment of Okinawa, to conduct scientific research, and to help conserve the environment by working with the community and providing educational opportunities.</p>\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> 目標 </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  \r\n                       1. 沖縄島全域を対象とした環境モニタリングサイトの構築 \r\n                       2. サンプル処理システムの構築\r\n                       3. 沖縄の生物多様性の基礎資料の蓄積\r\n                       4. 沖縄の地域環境教育ネットワークの構築       \r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n\r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel3">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">\r\n         これまでに行った調査          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1368.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> ２０１６年４月１日より、２４調査区で７２基＋３基、合計７５基のトラップが稼働中<br>\r\n                   ２０１６年３月１３日時点で、６００超のボトルを回収、１８０万頭を超える昆虫が採集され、うち、９０％以上が目までのソート完了</p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel2">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">\r\n         スタッフ          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_1368.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n         </div>\r\n              <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> コーディネーター </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> ソーティングチーム </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> 芳田琢磨率いる６人のチームでサイトの維持管理とサンプル回収、ソーティングを担当 </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel4">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">\r\n          ご協力いただいている機関や個人        \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n          <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <img class="img-responsive text-center padding-20" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_0996.jpg" />\r\n                </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="row">\r\n                 <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> うるま市役所、大宜味村、大山田芋関係者、沖縄県庁、沖縄県教育庁、沖縄県立博物館、沖縄県北部農林水産振興センター、浦添高等学校、球陽高等学校、沖縄県立教育センター、首里高等学校、名護高等学校、普天間高等学校、辺土名高等学校、沖縄国際大学、沖縄こどもの国、沖縄市、沖縄市郷土博物館、沖縄タイムス社、恩納村、恩納村博物館、カリフォルニア科学アカデミー、国頭村、森林総合研究所九州支所、タイフーンFM、高嶺英恒、嵩原建二、玉城青少年の家、千葉県立中央博物館、北谷町、TBS、東南植物楽園、中城公園、名護市勝山区、名護市、名護博物館、南城市、東村、東村立山と水の生活博物館、慶佐次地区評議会、兵庫県立人と自然の博物館、北海道大学、北海道大学総合博物館、マダガスカル生物多様性センター、森の家みんみん、やんばる学びの森、やんばる野生生物保護センター ウフギー自然館、琉球新報、琉球大学、琉球放送\r\n </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n    \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n           \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n          [:]', '[:en]About[:ja]概要[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '19-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-02 02:48:01', '2016-08-02 02:48:01', '', 19, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=691', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(692, 1, '2016-08-02 03:49:06', '2016-08-02 03:49:06', '<div class="row" id="front-icons-wrapper margin-bottom50">\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Achievements</h2>\r\n<hr class="home2 left">\r\n\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<h2>Achievement of the OKEON Project Field and Social Networks in FY2015 </h2>\r\n\r\n<div class="panel-group" id="accordion">\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel1">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">\r\n          Summary      \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n       <div class="row">\r\n               \r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20">  \r\n                       + 24 research sites with 72 SLAM traps are established.\r\n+ The system is established for collecting the material and data from 72 traps every two weeks and maintaining those traps.\r\n+ The sorting and curatorial systems for the materials are established.\r\n+ Met and had meetings with more than 150+ Okinawan people.\r\n+ Cooperating with 28+ groups.\r\n+ One report in the Research Bulletin of Environmental Education Center, Miyagi University of Education.\r\n+ Nine media releases.\r\n+ Yoshi has been selected as a committee member for an Okinawan prefectural project, the controlling invasive species.\r\n+ Yoshi has been offered having six columns on a newspaper, Ryukyu Shinpo, for six months (once a month).\r\n                      \r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n\r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="panel panel-default" id="panel3">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">\r\n         Sampling          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n         <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                   <p class="intro left padding-20">  \r\n                   + Lab space for sorting material and cabinets for the specimens were set up.\r\n+ 600+ collection events, 6,000+ sorted vials, and more than 180,000+ insect specimens have been accumulated.\r\n+ One technician and six staffs in the sorting team have been hired.\r\n+ The sorting staffs have been quickly trained and more than 90% of the insect samples are sorted into the order level on time.\r\n+ Reference collection of Okinawan ants was gifted from Mr. Takamine.\r\n+ Three undetermined species of ants are recognized from the sample collected in the ants research program at the high schools.   \r\n                  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel4">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">\r\n          Networking     \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">\r\n          <div class="row">\r\n                 <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                  <h3 class="data-theme"> OKEON project has been cooperating with at least 28 groups listed below </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left"> \r\n<span class = ''bold''> + Tsuji Lab at University of Ryukyus </span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>The main counter part for MOU. Two jointed grant proposals have been submitted. Jointed lab meetings were taken place. Planning with them that making theses using material from OKEON project.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Subtropical Field Science Center at University of Ryukyus</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Helping establishment of the field sites at Oku, Yona, and two at the Campus in the Univ. of Ryukyus.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Ryukyu University Museum, Fujukan</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Giving us advices on the curatorial system, on site localities, and connecting to the Okinawan community of conservation biology.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Okinawa Prefectural Museum</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing us a cold space for storing specimens. Cooperation on their exhibition is planning.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Se-fa Utakim, the world heritage</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Kurashiki Dam</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Nago Central Park</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Nakagusuku Park</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site. Suggested us some connections in the Okinawan society.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Okinawa Prefectural Forest Park</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Heiwasozo-no-mori Park</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site</span>	\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Tamagusuku Youth and Children''s Center</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site, and they are willing the cooperation with us on development of an environmental education program.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Hentona High School</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site. Established an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Kyuyo High School</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Established an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa. We found several undetermined ant species in their material.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Futenma High School</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Established an ant research team in their biology club program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa. We found an undetermined ant species in their material. It is the species, which is at least the first record in Japan.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Kaiho High School</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Established an ant research team in their class program, and their research were selected in the 36th Exhibition of the Science-work by the students in Okinawa.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Higashi Museum</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Helping us to get the permission to set up a site at the mangrove forest in Higashi son.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Community at the mangrove forest in Kesaji Gulf, National Heritage</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>They have accepted setting a site up at the mangrove forest area, and planning using the site for the local environmental education.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Bird Forest Nature Park, Uruma City</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Nago Museum</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site and helping us to get the permission to set up a site at the Mt. Katsu-dake in Nago City.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Onna-Son Museum</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Discussing the way to cooperation for the research on the natural history in the village.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Okinawa City Museum</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site, and cooperated on their exhibition, helped us to make multiple connections to Okinawan Society, planning cooperation on their new exhibition.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Chatan Town Hall</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site, gave us suggestions for setting soil sensors.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Sueyoshi Park (Naha City)</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site, helped us to find a site in Sueyoshi Park.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Mori-no-ie Minmin</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Helped us to find a site in Sueyoshi Park.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Yambaru Discovery Forest</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Southeast Botanical Gardens</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Ohyama Yam Farm</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Providing a site.</span>\r\n<span class = ''bold''>+ Mr. Takamine</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>Provided the reference collection of Okinawan ants.</span>\r\n\r\n　　　　　　　　　　　</p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n    \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel5">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive">\r\n         Publications          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n            \r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <p class="intro left padding-20"> <span class = ''bold''>Yoshimura M, Yoshida T, Ogasawara M & Economo E (<em>in press</em>)</span> Ant Research Program for High School Students Using the Time-unit Sampling Method. Research Bulletin of Environmental Education Center,Miyagi University of Education.  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="panel panel-default" id="panel2">\r\n    <div class="panel-heading">\r\n      <h4 class="panel-title">\r\n        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">\r\n         Media Release          \r\n        </a>\r\n      </h4>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">\r\n      <div class="panel-body">        \r\n            \r\n           <div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Newspaper </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left"> \r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Nov 16 Ryukyu Shinpo</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Nov 28 Okinawa Times</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Dec 04 Ryukyu Shinpo</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2016 Jan 29 Ryukyu Shinpo</span>\r\n  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> TV </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left"> \r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Nov 26 RBC News</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Dec 16 RBC News</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2016 Feb 28 TBS Bessatsu Asahi Journal</span>\r\n  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12">\r\n                    <h3 class="padding-left-20 data-theme"> Radio </h3>\r\n                    <p class="intro left"> \r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Oct 15 Typhoon FM Hitowaku</span>\r\n<span class = ''padding-left-20''>2015 Nov 15 Typhoon FM Magical Mystery Tour</span>\r\n  </p>\r\n                </div>      \r\n           </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n           \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n          \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '[:en]Achievements[:ja]業績[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '620-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-02 03:49:06', '2016-08-02 03:49:06', '', 620, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=692', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(693, 1, '2016-08-02 03:55:03', '2016-08-02 03:55:03', '[:en]<img class="aligncenter wp-image-697" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_2855-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_2855" width="500" height="375" />\r\nFollowing on from the success of Dr Yoshimura’s column in the Ryukyu Shinpo, OIST hosted a joint event on Sunday 31st July featuring Dr Yoshimura himself. Attendees were able to meet Dr Yoshimura, listen to his experiences as a researcher both in Japan and overseas in the USA, and learn how to use a magnifying glass to spot different types of ants.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-698" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_2861-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_2861" width="500" height="375" />\r\n\r\nDr. Yoshimura spoke about how he became a researcher, and in particular why he became interested in ants. He discussed his experiences moving to San Francisco, working as a researcher and the difficulties he faced. One of the ways that Dr Yoshimura coped living in the USA where there was limited funding for researchers was by starting a one-man band, the Male Ants Project, and earned extra money by busking. Event participants were treated to a performance by Dr Yoshimura of the popular Sukiyaki song.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-699" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_2900.jpg" alt="IMG_2900" width="500" height="375" />\r\n\r\nAfter the talk, participants were taught how to use a mini microscope to investigate which creatures were in their own surroundings, starting with the Inner Garden at OIST. Children who were already interested in ants or looking for a topic for their summer research project had the opportunity to hear from an expert researcher. Over 50 people attended, and the event was highly successful, with children, parents and university students alike engaged and interested.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-700" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_2929.jpg" alt="IMG_2929" width="500" height="375" />[:ja]Following on from the success of Dr Yoshimura’s column in the Ryukyu Shinpo, OIST hosted a joint event on Sunday 31st July featuring Dr Yoshimura himself. Attendees were able to meet Dr Yoshimura, listen to his experiences as a researcher both in Japan and overseas in the USA, and learn how to use a magnifying glass to spot different types of ants.\r\n\r\nDr. Yoshimura spoke about how he became a researcher, and in particular why he became interested in ants. He discussed his experiences moving to San Francisco, working as a researcher and the difficulties he faced. One of the ways that Dr Yoshimura coped living in the USA where there was limited funding for researchers was by starting a one-man band, the Male Ants Project, and earned extra money by busking. Event participants were treated to a performance by Dr Yoshimura of the popular Sukiyaki song.\r\n\r\nAfter the talk, participants were taught how to use a mini microscope to investigate which creatures were in their own surroundings, starting with the Inner Garden at OIST. Children who were already interested in ants or looking for a topic for their summer research project had the opportunity to hear from an expert researcher. Over 50 people attended, and the event was highly successful, with children, parents and university students alike engaged and interested.[:]', 'Ryukyu Shinpo Spin-Off Event in collaboration with OIST', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e6%97%a5%e6%9c%ac%e8%aa%9e-ryukyu-shinpo-spin-off-event-in-collaboration-with-oist', '', '', '2016-08-03 02:20:15', '2016-08-03 02:20:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-okeon/htdocs/?p=693', 0, 'post', '', 0),
